The paper deals with the problem of image super-resolution, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses generative adversarial networks (GANs) for unsupervised learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of deep models for up-sampling, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper involves image processing and manipulation, which falls under the graphics category (cs.GR). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on NTIRE2018 datasets, which is a common benchmark in multimedia (cs.MM).
